{
  "stem": "1736.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A shochet is a person that knows how to ritually-- I don't know whether I can put that properly-- comply with the ritual laws that-- how animals should be killed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I won't go into details, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said before, I was two years old when we arrived there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Soon after, a sister was born to-- well, a daughter was born to the family, which was my sister.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was born in 1928, in Dessau, where the hospital was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was two years younger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born in '26.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, at a later date, in 1935, another boy was born, my brother, who was Norbert Nissan.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, unfortunately, both of them perished later on in the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was our family, as it--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The immediate family that we had.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had-- in Dessau, on the other hand, we had some relatives, in the sense that there weren't brothers, or sisters, or cousins, but they were slightly more distant.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had come from the same area in Poland where my parents came from, and in fact, like I said, they were second or third cousins.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were sort of visiting them quite regularly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fact was that I stayed with them on a regular basis on holidays, when, even though my parents might not be there, I would stay there overnight, and, you know, thus enable me to go to shul more often, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- there was a grandmother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My grandfather died, both sides.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never knew them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My grandmother was alive, but she passed away in 1937.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I only knew her from visiting Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
